description:
Bug 38131ajc needs -d. I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have to do something with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler. Create a class in a subpackage such as:
package subpackage;
public class Test {
public static void main(String[] args) {
System.out.println("Hello");
}
}
Then compile using the following command: ajc subpackage\Test.java
You will see a directory "subpackage" created under the existing "subpackage" directory. subpackage\Test.java or javac subpackage\Test.java. No big deal, really.

SR:
To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Create a Java class in a subpackage, for example:
   package subpackage;
   public class Test {
       public static void main(String[] args) {
           System.out.println("Hello");
       }
   }
2. Compile the class using the following command:
   ajc subpackage\Test.java
3. Observe the creation of a directory named "subpackage" under the existing "subpackage" directory.
